Networking Basics

This file contains fundamental networking commands and interpretations for Linux.  

ip a
ip addr
ping -c google.com
ip a
traceroute google.com
ip route
ss -tuln (open port)
ss -tunp (active connections)

t - tcp
u - udp
-l -listening sockets
-n - numeric output

3/8/25
TOOLS USED 
Wireshark, tcpdump, ping

LESSON : ARP
Purpose: Maps IP addresses (Layer 3) to MAC addresses (Layer 2).
Example Packets:
Who has 10.0.0.5? Tell 10.0.0.1
10.0.0.5 is at 08:00:27:4e:8b:3c
Wireshark Filter: arp

ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol)
		Purpose: Diagnostics and error reporting (ping/traceroute).
		Example Packets:
		Echo (ping) request
		Echo (ping) reply
		Wireshark Filter: icmp

command learnt 
Ping Windows from Kali
ping -c 4 <X.x.x..x>

Capture ARP & ICMP packets
sudo tcpdump -i enp0s1 -c 20 arp or icmp
